# Start the monitoring as a background job
$job = Start-Job -ScriptBlock {
    # Import the function definition (if needed, but we defined it in the current session so we can dot source a script file)
    # Alternatively, we can define the function inside the script block again.
    # But note: the function uses variables defined in the outer scope, so we need to pass them in or redefine.

    # Let's redefine the function and variables inside the script block to avoid scope issues.
    $monitorLog = "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025\11_SYSTEMIC_ANALYSIS\monitor_log.txt"
    $watchPath = "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025"
    $suspiciousKeywords = @(
        "delete", "remove", "alter", "tamper", "modify", "corrupt",
        "access denied", "permission", "block", "restrict", "error",
        "unauthorized", "security", "audit", "investigation"
    )

    function Start-CaseMonitoring {
        Write-Host "=== CASE MONITORING ACTIVATED ===" -ForegroundColor Red
        Write-Host "Monitoring: $watchPath" -ForegroundColor Yellow
        Write-Host "Log File: $monitorLog" -ForegroundColor Yellow

        # Initial system snapshot
        $initialState = Get-ChildItem $watchPath -Recurse -File |
            Select-Object Name, Length, LastWriteTime, FullName
        $initialState | Export-Csv "$watchPath\11_SYSTEMIC_ANALYSIS\initial_snapshot.csv" -NoTypeInformation

        # Continuous monitoring loop
        while ($true) {
            $currentTime = Get-Date -Format "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss"
            $currentState = Get-ChildItem $watchPath -Recurse -File

            # Check for file changes
            foreach ($file in $currentState) {
                $logEntry = "$currentTime | $($file.Name) | Size: $($file.Length) | Modified: $($file.LastWriteTime)"
                Add-Content -Path $monitorLog -Value $logEntry
            }

            # Check system events for suspicious activity
            Get-EventLog -LogName System -After (Get-Date).AddMinutes(-5) -EntryType Error,Warning |
            Where-Object { $_.Message -match ($suspiciousKeywords -join '|') } |
            ForEach-Object {
                $alert = "SECURITY ALERT: $($_.TimeGenerated) | $($_.Message)"
                Add-Content -Path $monitorLog -Value $alert
                Write-Host $alert -ForegroundColor Red
            }

            Start-Sleep -Seconds 300  # Check every 5 minutes
        }
    }

    Start-CaseMonitoring
}

$ExtractedFile = "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025\04_EVIDENCE_DOCUMENTS\Genspark_Disclosure_Analysis_Clean.txt"
if (Test-Path $ExtractedFile) {
    $FileSize = (Get-Item $ExtractedFile).Length
    Write-Host "Extracted file size: $($FileSize / 1KB) KB" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    
    # Read the content
    $ExtractedContent = Get-Content $ExtractedFile -Raw
    $LineCount = ($ExtractedContent -split "`n").Count
    Write-Host "Line count: $LineCount" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    
    # Check if we have meaningful content
    if ($LineCount -gt 10) {
        Write-Host "✅ MEANINGFUL CONTENT FOUND - PROCEEDING WITH ANALYSIS" -ForegroundColor Green
        
        # Extract sections that might contain disclosure comparisons
        Write-Host "`n=== SEARCHING FOR DISCLOSURE COMPARISON SECTIONS ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan
        
        # Look for patterns indicating version comparisons
        $ComparisonPatterns = @(
            "version 1.*version 2",
            "original.*modified", 
            "first.*second",
            "disclosure.*difference",
            "changed.*from",
            "alteration",
            "modification"
        )
        
        $ComparisonResults = @()
        foreach ($pattern in $ComparisonPatterns) {
            $matches = [regex]::Matches($ExtractedContent, $pattern, "IgnoreCase")
            foreach ($match in $matches) {
                # Get context around the match
                $start = [Math]::Max(0, $match.Index - 100)
                $length = [Math]::Min(300, $ExtractedContent.Length - $start)
                $context = $ExtractedContent.Substring($start, $length)
                $ComparisonResults += [PSCustomObject]@{
                    Pattern = $pattern
                    Context = $context
                    Position = $match.Index
                }
            }
        }
        
        if ($ComparisonResults.Count -gt 0) {
            Write-Host "✅ FOUND $($ComparisonResults.Count) COMPARISON REFERENCES" -ForegroundColor Green
            
            # Create side-by-side analysis
            Write-Host "`n=== SIDE-BY-SIDE COMPARISON ANALYSIS ===" -ForegroundColor Yellow
            
            $ComparisonResults | Sort-Object Position | ForEach-Object {
                Write-Host "`n--- COMPARISON: $($_.Pattern) ---" -ForegroundColor Cyan
                Write-Host "CONTEXT: $($_.Context)" -ForegroundColor White
            }
            
            # Save comparison analysis
            $ComparisonResults | Export-Csv "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025\04_EVIDENCE_DOCUMENTS\Disclosure_Comparison_Analysis.csv" -NoTypeInformation
            Write-Host "`n✅ Comparison analysis saved to CSV" -ForegroundColor Green
        } else {
            Write-Host "❌ No direct comparison patterns found" -ForegroundColor Red
        }
        
    } else {
        Write-Host "❌ EXTRACTED CONTENT APPEARS EMPTY - NEED ALTERNATIVE APPROACH" -ForegroundColor Red
    }

powershell
# Alternative approach - search the raw Genspark HTML for specific content
Write-Host "`n=== ALTERNATIVE DISCLOSURE EXTRACTION ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan

$GensparkPath = "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025\10_DISCLOSURE_REVIEWS\Genspark - 2nd Disclosure review3RD4TH5 6.html"
if (Test-Path $GensparkPath) {
    $RawContent = Get-Content $GensparkPath -Raw
    
    # Look for specific case content patterns
    Write-Host "Searching for case-specific content..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    
    # Search for content between specific HTML tags that might contain disclosure text
    $ContentPatterns = @(
        '<div[^>]*>(.*?)</div>',
        '<p[^>]*>(.*?)</p>',
        '<span[^>]*>(.*?)</span>',
        '<td[^>]*>(.*?)</td>'
    )
    
    $AllTextContent = @()
    foreach ($pattern in $ContentPatterns) {
        $matches = [regex]::Matches($RawContent, $pattern, "IgnoreCase")
        foreach ($match in $matches) {
            # Extract just the text content (remove HTML tags inside)
            $innerContent = $match.Groups[1].Value
            $cleanText = [regex]::Replace($innerContent, "<[^>]+>", "")
            if ($cleanText.Trim().Length -gt 20) {
                $AllTextContent += $cleanText.Trim()
            }
        }
    }
    
    Write-Host "Extracted $($AllTextContent.Count) text segments" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    
    # Filter for disclosure-related content
    $DisclosureContent = $AllTextContent | Where-Object { 
        $_ -match "disclosure|evidence|Longo|case|charge|version" 
    }
    
    Write-Host "Found $($DisclosureContent.Count) disclosure-related segments" -ForegroundColor Green
    
    if ($DisclosureContent.Count -gt 0) {
        Write-Host "`n=== DISCLOSURE CONTENT SAMPLES ===" -ForegroundColor Yellow
        $DisclosureContent[0..4] | ForEach-Object {
            Write-Host "• $($_.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(150, $_.Length))..." -ForegroundColor White
